    HEADLINE
    ────────
    Hands in the Clay on Beaufort Street

    ANGLE
    ─────
    Perth Pottery Co is an owner-operated hand-building studio on Beaufort Street in Inglewood, where Elizabeth and her team run classes built around coil, pinch, and slab rather than the wheel. The format flexes between Thursday sessions with herbal tea and weekend Sip and Pot evenings with wine, and firing is included — a low-friction entry point for beginners who want to leave with something they actually made. There's a story here about a small, independent craft studio shaping how Perth newcomers meet clay for the first time.

